tia.ca/news/release/?id=20200315002 |archive-date=March 18, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> <br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=03|day1=11|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| location        = [[Nova Scotia]], [[Canada]]\n}}\nThe '''2020 coronavirus pandemic in Nova Scotia''' is an ongoing viral pandemic of [[coronavirus disease 2019]] (COVID-19), a novel infectious disease caused by [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2]] (SARS-CoV-2). {{As of|2020|04|13|df=US}}, the [[Canada|Canadian]] province of [[Nova Scotia]] has the fifth-most number of cases of [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Canada|COVID-19 in Canada]] during the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|2019\u201320 worldwide pandemic]]. {{As of|2020|04|13|df=US}}, there have been 473 confirmed cases, 101 recoveries, three deaths, and 15,580 negative tests.<ref name=\"novascotia1\"/><ref name=\"coronavirus/#cases\"/>\n__TOC__\n\n== Timeline ==\n<onlyinclude>\n{{Medical cases chart\n|barwidth=medium\n|numwidth=tw\n\n|disease=COVID-19\n|location=Nova Scotia\n|outbreak=2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic\n\n|togglesbar=\n<div class=\"nomobile\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|mar}}\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|apr}}\n<span class=\"mw-collapsible mw-customtoggle-l15 mw-customtoggle-mar-l15 mw-collapsed\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-l15\" style=\"padding:0 8px\">Last 15 days</span>\n<span class=\"mw-collapsible mw-customtoggle-l15 mw-customtoggle-mar-l15\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-l15\" style=\"border:2px solid lightblue; padding:0 8px\">Last 15 days</span>\n</div>\n|rows=\n{{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-15|||3|||3|firstright1=y|divisor=1.8|numwidth=tw|collapsible=y}}\n{{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-16|||5|||5|+67%|divisor=1.8|numwidth=tw|collapsible=y}}\n{{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-17|||7|||7|+40%|divisor=1.8|numwidth=tw|collapsible=y}}\n{{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-18|||12|||12|+71%|divisor=1.8|numwidth=tw|collapsible=y}