y well turn out to be the most enjoyable new show of the summer.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://time.com/5619221/florida-girls-review-pop-tv/|title=Florida Girls Is the Most Fun You'll Have in Front of the TV This Summer|first=Judy|last=Berman|publisher=[[Time_(magazine)|Time]]|date=July 9, 2019|accessdate=July 19, 2019}}</ref> [[The New York Times|''The New York Times'']] described the show as \"more endearing than challenging, more amiable than thought-provoking, clever enough to engage but not necessarily funny enough to enchant.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/09/arts/television/florida-girls-review-pop.html|title=Review: \u2018Florida Girls\u2019 Is Another Reason to Find the Pop Network|first=Mike|last=Hale|publisher=[[The New York Times]]|date=July 9, 2019|accessdate=July 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|8548870}}\n\n{{Pop (U.S. TV network) programming}}\n\n[[Category:2010s American sitcoms]]\n[[Category:2019 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2019 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television series by 3 Arts Entertainment]] \n[[Category:Television series by Lionsgate Television]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Florida]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Florida Girls\n| image                    = Florida Girls Title Card.jpg\n| caption                  = \n| creator                  = Laura Chinn\n| starring                 = Laura Chinn<br>Patty Guggenheim<br>Laci Mosley<br>[[Melanie Field]]\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = 1\n| num_episodes             = 10\n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = {{Plainlist|\n*Laura Chinn\n*Jared Miller\n*Tony Hernandez\n*Lilly Burns\n*Oly Obst\n*Josh Lieberman\n}}\n| camera                   = [[Single-camera setup|Single]]\n| runtime                  = 22 minutes\n| company                  = JAX Media<br>3 Arts Entertainment<br>[[Lionsgate Television]]\n| channel                  = [[Pop (U.S. TV network)|Pop]]\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2019|7|10}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|2019|8|7}}\n| website                  = https://poptv.com/floridagirls\n}}\n'''''Florida Girls''''' is an American sitcom created by and starring Laura Chinn. The series premiered on [[Pop (U.S. TV network)|Pop]] on July 10, 2019.\n\nOn October 3, 2019, the series was renewed for a second season, <ref>{{cite web|title=Pop TV Renews Critically Acclaimed \"Florida Girls\" for Second Season|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/10/03/pop-tv-renews-critically-acclaimed-florida-girls-for-second-season-938215/20191003pop01/|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=October 3, 2019}}</ref> but on March 3, 2020, Pop cancelled the show along with several other originals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/pop-pulls-plug-florida-girls-best-intentions-flack-questions-scripted-future-1202874777/|title=Pop Pulls the Plug On \u2018Florida Girls\u2019, \u2018Best Intentions\u2019 & \u2018Flack\u2019, Raising Questions About Net\u2019s Scripted Future|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=2020-03-05|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n==Synopsis==\n''Florida Girls'' follows a group of four women, who live in a trailer park in Florida. When one of their friends receives her [[General Educational Development|GED]] and moves out of state, Shelby becomes unsatisfied with the status quo, and aspires to do the same with her friends.\n\n==Cast==\n*Laura Chinn as Shelby\n*[[Melanie Field]] as Kaitlin \n*Patty Guggenheim as Erica\n*Laci Mosley as Jayla\n*Patrick Roper as Ken\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table\n|background=#\n|overall= \n|title=|titleR=<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/showatch/florida-girls/listings|title=Shows A-Z - florida girls on pop|work=the Futon Critic|acce